  "text": "In recent years, people have put forward different security routing protocols. Most of these are based on the traditional security mechanisms of the cryptosystems, which need much more memory and energy consumption. The wireless sensor network is composed of many small sensor nodes with limited bandwidth and stringent node constraints in terms of power and memory. What is more, the cryptosystems can only resist external attack; once internal nodes have mutations or attacks, they will not be able to be identified. So the traditional cryptosystems of traditional security mechanisms are not fully applicable to wireless sensor networks [CITATION_1] .",
